Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: qcom: common: enable jack detection for MI2S DAI links

qcom_snd_wcd_jack_setup() only calls snd_soc_component_set_jack() for
TX_CODEC_DMA DAI types. On boards using MI2S with external codecs that
have jack detection (like ES8326), the codec's jack is never connected,
so IRQ-based jack detection is silently ignored.

Add MI2S DAI cases so codecs on MI2S links get their jack set up.

Based on upstream patch by Hongyang Zhao:
https://lore.kernel.org/linux-arm-msm/20260305-rubikpi-next-20260304-v1-4-327595a4528a@thundersoft.com/
---
 sound/soc/qcom/common.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/qcom/common.c b/sound/soc/qcom/common.c
--- a/sound/soc/qcom/common.c
+++ b/sound/soc/qcom/common.c
@@ -226,6 +226,8 @@
 	}

 	switch (cpu_dai->id) {
+	case PRIMARY_MI2S_RX ... QUATERNARY_MI2S_TX:
+	case QUINARY_MI2S_RX ... QUINARY_MI2S_TX:
 	case TX_CODEC_DMA_TX_0:
 	case TX_CODEC_DMA_TX_1:
 	case TX_CODEC_DMA_TX_2:
